	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=119423'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
Sebat2004</a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Newbie<br>
			
				Posts: 7<br>
				
				Registered: 10-11-2005
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=119423'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=beastlordbalance&message.id=3547#M3547">1</a> of 12
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 301 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV><SPAN class=postbody><FONT size=2>I've been playing with aggro reduction trying to stay out of the HoTT box on raids. I'm an 8k+, nearly 1700 AC unbuffed BST with just over 1000 AA now <A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=739068" target=_blank>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=739068</A>&nbsp;&nbsp; Max avoidance and mitigation AA's, and 65 avoidance on my gear, and I shouldn't be out-tanking or aggroing a similarily geared and AA'd plate tank.&nbsp; I'm getting really tired of dying on raids becuase of broke taunt and not being able to shed aggro.&nbsp; Hopefully the changes in today's patch help the taunt problems.<BR><BR>Beastlords have only one skill they can use to reduce aggro, Roar of Thunder, and the maximum it can reduce hate is 2250 every 15 min if you spend 18 AA to max it (7.5 min if you spend 25 AA on maxing hastened thunder). That is the only ability a Beastlord has to reduce aggro other than procs from weapons, and many of those weapons do not compare to mid-level raiding content ratios (an 18 dmg, 20 dly ratio is not my idea of a "good" weapon).&nbsp; If I use my 855dd proc weapon, I can just plan on getting aggro and killing one or more people if the mob turns on enrage or has high riposte damage.<BR><BR>There are 2 Beastlord pet spells, however, that list a 50 hate reduction in the description, Spirit of Flame Strike and Spirit of Snow Strike. Everything I've ever read says that this ONLY affects a Beastlords pet, as it's your pet that procs it, and not you. However, I did try it out on the last Time raid, and watched for my name very closely in the HoTT box, and I don't believe I was in it on any of the bosses for the duration of the fight, so I'm wondering if it does actually help. </FONT></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV><SPAN class=postbody><FONT size=2></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><SPAN class=postbody><FONT size=2>We have a lot of new aggro-generating abilities, including Rake from PoR, but no better way to reduce the aggro.&nbsp; As it stands now, I usually end up tanking in RSS and equivalent zones becuase the "tank" can't keep aggro, and I've built my toon around the tanking beast mentality.&nbsp; I'm not supposed to be tanking, so please, please, please... enable me to shed some aggro so a plate tank can keep the mobs attention.&nbsp; I am not looking for a reduction in my DPS capabilies by any means.</FONT></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV><SPAN class=postbody><FONT size=2></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><SPAN class=postbody><FONT size=2>Yes, I could nuke less, use fewer DPS AA's/Discs, wait longer to engage, etc... But I fail to understand how, and why, a Beastlord doing ~300 DPS on a raid mob&nbsp;should get aggro from simply meleeing and nuking a mob that others are doing 400+ on but have the means to reduce aggro with a jolt, FD, evade, or other similar&nbsp;ability.&nbsp; </FONT></SPAN><SPAN class=postbody><BR><BR><FONT size=2>I'm not bad at digging for info and research, but any help anyone wants to provide in discovering the truth, please feel free. I've been looking at raw spell data, scouring message boards, everything... and I'm just not finding a difinitive answer on it that satisfies me. </FONT></SPAN></DIV>
<P><SPAN class=postbody><FONT size=2>Some rambling :</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN class=postbody><FONT size=2>If our pet damage aggro adds to ours, why wouldn't a hate reduciton spell from our pet affect us?? <BR><BR>Wouldn't the DD and stun part of the pet proc negate the advantage of the hate reduction? Although all of our other pet procs have a DD/stun component in them as well as having a hate component in them. <BR><BR>If we use a pet to attack something, and it dies, we get the aggro. So what does that say about how pet hate affects its owner??<BR></FONT></SPAN><SPAN class=postbody><FONT size=2></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN class=postbody><FONT size=2>A jolt-type spell would be wonderful... </FONT></SPAN></P>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>06-13-2006</span> <span class=time_text>10:19 AM</span>
